data.text:
Tsletsi Airport is a large airport in Djelfa, Algeria. The airport is located at latitude 34.66563 and longitude 3.35198. The airport has 2 runways: 3/21 and 7/25. The ICAO airport code of this field is DAFI. The airport's IATA code is QDJ. Nearby other airfields are Ain Oussera Airport, Bou Saada Airport, Laghouat - Molay Ahmed Medeghri Airport, Ras el Miaad Airport and Abdelhafid Boussouf Bou Chekif Airport.

Tsletsi Airport does not publish a METAR, the nearest weather station is Bou Saada Airport, which is 107 km away. The flight information region (FIR) is Alger.

Tsletsi Airport is in the timezone of Africa/Algiers. Difference with UTC is +1 h. Today the sun rises at 06:05 and sets at 19:37. This applies to Tsletsi Airport, the universal daylight period may be different. The difference between the local time and UTC is +1 hour. Daylight saving time is currently in progress.

Things to do at this airport

Go to Vliegles.nl to find flying lessons, skydives and other flying experiences. Browse the page for all available activities near Tsletsi Airport. You can also use the search function to find specific flying lessons, skydives or other flying experiences near your place.

On this airport you can find flying clubs. The only known company on this field is Aero Club Hauts Plateaux.
